<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2928] Fix Hinted Handoff replay</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2928</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Broken in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2668&quot; title=&quot;don&amp;#39;t perform HH to client-mode nodes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2668&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2668&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Brandon explains:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;the Ack and Ack2 verb handlers are applying a new ep state every time there is a generation change via Gossiper.applyStateLocally, so it&apos;s always unset initially when the node starts up. state.hasToken() is set in the Gossiper&apos;s status check, which won&apos;t have happened when the onAlive event is sent to SS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
